author: wn.com
title: Anger at Stephen Harper, disenfranchisement fuelled aboriginal voter turnout, say activists
text: Aboriginal activists who spent months mobilizing First Nations communities say outgoing Prime Minister Stephen Harper's attempt to disenfranchise aboriginal voters backfired and fuelled turnout so high that some reserves ran out of ballots. ...
